parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
Spare tire failure can cause accidents, injuries, and strand the driver.
Tire blowout can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
Tire belt shift can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
Tire noise and vibration can cause discomfort and affect vehicle handling.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slip or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward
and the vehicle may not shift into gear or may get stuck in one gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to slip or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unexplained acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
the vehicle accelerates without the accelerator pedal being pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can roll away unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls backward or forward when parked on an incline
the vehicle rolls away when the transmission is in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Cruise Control Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
and may not respond to braking or attempts to disengage the cruise control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fire Hazard due to Cruise Control Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause a fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke appears from under the hood
and the vehicle may catch fire

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inability to Repair due to Lack of Parts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of available parts for the cruise control recall repair can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Dealerships are unable to repair the vehicle due to a lack of available parts
leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.
